### [2 Chronicles Chapter 3](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#001.md)

[2 Chronicles 3:1](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">ch2 3:1</span></span>

Moriah - It was the belief of the ancient Jews, that the temple was
built on that very place, where Abraham offered up Issac.

[2 Chronicles 3:3](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">ch2 3:3</span></span>

Instructed - By David, and by the Spirit of God. The measure - According
to he measure which was first fixed.

[2 Chronicles 3:4](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">ch2 3:4</span></span>

The height - This being a kind of turret to the building.

[2 Chronicles 3:5](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">ch2 3:5</span></span>

Greater house - The holy place, which was thrice as large as the holy of
holies.

[2 Chronicles 3:9](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">ch2 3:9</span></span>

Nails - Each of the nails, screws, or pins, by which the golden plates
were fastened to the walls, weighed, or rather was worth, fifty shekels,
workmanship and all. Upper chambers - Rather, the roof.

[2 Chronicles 3:10](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">ch2 3:10</span></span>

Image work - Or, of moveable work, not fixed to the mercy - seat, as the
Mosaical cherubim, but in a moving posture. It seems, they were designed
to represent the angels, who attend the Divine Majesty.

[2 Chronicles 3:13](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">ch2 3:13</span></span>

Inward - Heb. towards the house, that is, the most holy house.

[2 Chronicles 3:14](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">ch2 3:14</span></span>

The veil - The inner veil before the most holy place. This denoted the
darkness of that dispensation and the distance at which the worshippers
were kept. But at the death of Christ this veil was rent; for thro' him
we are brought nigh, and have boldness, or liberty, not only to look,
but to enter into the holiest.

[2 Chronicles 3:17](../../../bib/kjv/ch2003.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">ch2 3:17</span></span>

Jachin - That is, He shall establish. Boaz - That is, In it is strength.

